    {
      "id": "51a01b8a-6641-4ba2-b4c7-64688930de95",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Results show that models created on sub-populations outperform a general model trained on all instances. Combining LMS and enrollment also outperforms other options. Moreover, there is no best model for all scenarios, but authors argue tree-based or rule-based models for interpretability purposes.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "51a01b8a-6641-4ba2-b4c7-64688930de95",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
